🧠 Projection in Spring Data JPA (SCN Format)
📌 Concept
Projection = Fetch only required fields instead of the entire entity.
Helps reduce:
Memory usage
Query execution time
Used when you don’t need full entity data

⚙️ Approach
🔹 Types of Projections
Type
Description
Interface-based
Uses interface with getter methods
Class-based (DTO)
Uses custom class with constructor
Dynamic Projection
Decide projection at runtime


💻 Code
1. ✅ Interface-Based Projection (Most Common)
public interface ProductView {
    String getTitle();
    double getPrice();
}

Repository:
List<ProductView> findByPriceGreaterThan(double price);

👉 Hibernate returns only title & price

2. ✅ Class-Based Projection (DTO)
public class ProductDTO {
    private String title;
    private double price;

    public ProductDTO(String title, double price) {
        this.title = title;
        this.price = price;
    }
}

Repository:
@Query("SELECT new com.example.ProductDTO(p.title, p.price) FROM Product p")
List<ProductDTO> getProducts();


3. ✅ Dynamic Projection
<T> List<T> findByTitle(String title, Class<T> type);

Usage:
repo.findByTitle("Laptop", ProductView.class);
repo.findByTitle("Laptop", ProductDTO.class);


🔑 Key Points
Projection avoids fetching unnecessary columns
Works with:
Derived queries
JPQL (@Query)
Interface-based:
No constructor needed
Faster & cleaner
DTO-based:
More control
Needed for complex logic

⚠️ Common Mistakes
❌ Getter names not matching entity fields
❌ Missing constructor in DTO
❌ Using projection but still fetching full entity (wrong query)
❌ Nested projection confusion

🧩 When to Use
Situation
Use
Only few fields needed
Interface Projection
Custom response object
DTO Projection
Flexible return type
Dynamic Projection


🎯 Learnings / Interview Angle
Q: Why use projection instead of entity?
👉 Fetching full entity is expensive → projection improves performance
Q: Which is better: Interface or DTO?
👉 Interface = simple cases
👉 DTO = complex queries / transformations

🚀 Bonus Tip
Projection is heavily used in:
REST APIs (return limited data)
Pagination + sorting
Microservices (optimize payload size)


